&lt;P&gt;1) Sarcasm should be based on intelligence. A least act intelligently enough to use the term "nerf" correctly. You can't "nerf" something you don't already have. Since you don't have auto-ranged-attack, it could not possibly be nerfed. The *whine* of "nerf" often originates from children who know what they want, but it is suggested by anybody else that they should not get exactly that. It is part of shouting down the opposition, especially when used with the "you promised never to nerf" statement from SOE. The flames are from the children screaming "nerf", not the reasonable people looking for a solution suitible for everybody.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;2) I suggested a limiting factor in response to others that said it would be too powerful. That makes it an attempt to compromise, not an attack on your class, not a personal&amp;nbsp;attempt to limit the power of anybody. Disrespect me for a lot of things, but attempting to find middle ground is an attack on neither side and not deserving of that accusation.&lt;/P&gt;</description>
